Do a global search for non-word characters in a string:

Copy
let str = "Give This is a test!";
let patt1 = /\W/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \W metacharacter is used to find a non-word character.

A word character is a character from a-z, A-Z, 0-9, including the _ (underscore) character.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\W	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\W") or simply: /\W/
Syntax with modifiers
Copy
new RegExp("\\W", "g") or simply: /\W/g
